    }
  ],
  "readiness": "NEEDS_REWORK",
  "summary": "The TechSpec's architectural direction (hardening over the existing autonomy substrate, no second queue, projection-not-authority, instructional skills, durable cursors as a shared primitive) is sound and consistent with L-003/L-005/L-006/L-008 and ADR-001..006. However, several safety-critical contracts are underspecified — the new task-level terminal operator path against token-fenced active runs, synthetic-run concurrency, the `ClaimNextRun` spawn-circuit filter, the spawn-failure observer/reset call-sites, the public `MaintainCurrentRunID` projection seam, the operator-vs-agent authorization boundary on `/api/tasks/:id/complete|fail`, and a notification cursor primitive shipped without a concrete consumer — each of which can produce wrong-behavior tasks if generated as-is. Tighten these before producing `_tasks.md`."
}
